  <h3>Fish Killing techniques: </h3>
  <ul>
    <li>ikejime = live slaughter. Hit the brain with a long metal</li>
    <li>Shinkei-nuki = using a long metal insert from the tail to the head, along the spine</li>
    <li>The more the fish moves when it's being slauhgtered the more of the textures and sweetness go away. Less movement, better tasting fish</li>
    <li>Kaimin = sleeping. Accupuntured fish on a board. To put the fish in comatose state, to maximize the freshness, until right before the kill</li>
